-- Manila Water Reports a 9% Profit Gain on Higher Billing Volume
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-11-11T11:53:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-11/manila-water-reports-a-9-profit-gain-on-higher-billing-volume.html
Manila Water Co. (MWC) , the largest water
supplier in the Philippines, said profit rose 9 percent to 4.29
billion pesos ($98.4 million) in the nine-month period through
September on higher billing volume.  Revenue for the period rose 6 percent to 11.54 billion
pesos from a year earlier, the company that provides half of
 Manila â€™s water supplies said today in a statement. The shares
have fallen 21 percent this year in Manila compared with a 7
percent gain by the 20-member Bloomberg World Water Index  To contact the reporter on this story:
